				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-7007497#post-3916369</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-7007497/redacted-for-questionable-reasons#post-3916369</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sat, 18 Aug 2018 19:23:09 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Cyclopian</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1990708</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>This is all subjective, obviously, but I personally don't see anything that could be interpreted as mocking the original author or article. I can't identify any part of the article that could be interpreted as a way of saying &quot;This is why Taboo sucks and you shouldn't like it&quot;. It's simply taking Taboo's main gimmick, exaggerating it, and playing it for comedy rather than horror.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-7007497#post-3916366</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-7007497/redacted-for-questionable-reasons#post-3916366</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sat, 18 Aug 2018 19:12:36 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>The Great Hippo</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3938622</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I think that's reasonable, and I can definitely understand downvoting an article on that basis.</p> <p>For my part, I'm very okay with this sort of thing when I'm fairly certain everyone adjacent to it is going to have a good laugh, and I know no one's going to walk away feeling attacked or hurt (which was definitely the case here).</p> <p>But I also think that disapproving of this on account of feeling like the <em>tone</em> is mean-spirited &#8212; even if no one involved feels targeted or maligned &#8212; is also pretty understandable. Especially if that tone is in-line with hostile articles posted in the past that <em>weren't</em> written purely in good fun and good faith.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
