				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-7007497#post-3916234</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-7007497/redacted-for-questionable-reasons#post-3916234</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sat, 18 Aug 2018 16:06:51 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>DrClef</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>213153</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>That's fine, I get it, and given the rating on the article, it seems that the general opinion on this one is positive. I still don't find it funny, probably because articles like this one give me PTSD flashbacks of the Old Fan days of mean-spirited &quot;MST&quot;ings and sporkings, as well as more vivid PTSD flashbacks of the Old SCP days of Decommissionings where the entire point was to mock the original author and make them feel bad.</p> <p>In any case, I've registered my distaste, everyone else seems to think it's okay, I'd rather not waste more time arguing over Which Guy Who Is Wrong On The Internet Is Actually Wrong.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
